Q.1] Write a Python program that prompts the user to input two numbers and raises a TypeError exception if the inputs are not numerical.


try:
    a = input("Enter first number: ")
    b = input("Enter second number: ")
    if not (a.replace('.', '', 1).isdigit() and b.replace('.', '', 1).isdigit()):
        raise TypeError("Inputs must be numbers")
    a = float(a)
    b = float(b)
    print("Numbers are:", a, b)
except TypeError as e:
    print("Error:", e)



Q2. Create a following DataFrame named as “data”. Write the python code for the following
a) Find all rows with the label “Pencil”. Extract all columns
b) Change the count of Eraser as 25 instead of 20.
c) List only the columns Company and Price.
d) List only rows with labels ‘Pencil’ and ‘Pen’
e) Delete column Count from the above DataFrame and display DataFrame..


import pandas as pd

data = pd.DataFrame
({
    "Item": ["Pencil", "Pencil", "Pen", "Pen", "Eraser"],
    "Company": ["Apsara", "Natraj", "Cello", "Parkar", "Apsara"],
    "Count": [15, 20, 25, 35, 20],
    "Price": [250, 200, 600, 900, 300]
})
print("Original DataFrame:\n", data)
print("\na) Pencil rows:\n", data[data["Item"] == "Pencil"])
data.loc[data["Item"] == "Eraser", "Count"] = 25
print("\nb) Updated DataFrame:\n", data)
print("\nc) Company and Price:\n", data[["Company", "Price"]])
print("\nd) Pencil and Pen rows:\n", data[data["Item"].isin(["Pencil", "Pen"])])
data = data.drop("Count", axis=1)
print("\ne) After deleting Count:\n", data)






